@node WhFor "Application"
@prev WhFor
@toc About

    @{b}@{fg highlight}What is the program for?@{fg text}@{ub}

    Polyglot  is,  generally, a program for @{b}learning foreign languages@{ub}.  But
it's  not  designed  for  learning  and testing the material prepared by the
author,  because  it  doesn't  include any ready material except one example
base.
    A person who's learning a new language mostly makes notes with new words
and  phrases.  Then learns it by repeating it with small parts.  It's a good
method, but using pencil and paper is not always comfortable.

    Polyglot  is  just  a  program  which  @{b}helps learning@{ub}.  You can create a
@{" base " link Basic}  containing  all  these  words and phrases, which may be divided into
smaller separated @{" groups " link Basic}.  You can learn it gradual, by one group, and add
new words in the same time.

    But  @{b}simple  words@{ub}  are  not  everything.   Often you need to learn some
@{b}groups@{ub}  of  similar  words,  e.g.   declination  of  verbs  or  many phrases
containing one word.  With Polyglot, you may create such tests.
    Also,  you  may - partly - learn more complex constructions and @{b}grammar@{ub},
by  completing gaps in sentences or convert one phrases into other.  You may
use the choosing test or just editing test.

@endnode

@node Possi "Possibilities"
@toc About

    @{b}@{fg highlight}What does Polyglot make possible@{fg text}@{ub}

    You  may @{b}create@{ub} new @{" bases " link Basic} containing different types of tests - simple
phrases,  editing  tests or choosing tests.  Then, you may @{b}change@{ub} and delete
existing  elements  and  @{b}add@{ub}  new to it.  You may @{b}save@{ub} and @{b}load@{ub} a whole base
from a disk.
    As  many  similar  programs,  Polyglot  lets  you  @{" learn " link LeTst}  @{b}new material@{ub}
(questions  are  asked  as  long  as  you  answer correctly) and @{" test " link LeTst} @{b}your
knowledge.@{ub}

@endnode

@node ForWh "Destination"
@toc About

    @{b}@{fg highlight}For whom is it designed@{fg text}@{ub}

    As this program doesn't @{b}learn@{ub} you, but @{b}helps you learning@{ub} yourself, it's
not  designed for children or beginners.  Persons who learn themselves, as I
wrote  @{" above " link WhFor},  may use it as a very comfortable alternative for pencil and
paper.

@endnode

@node Polyg "Advantages"
@next Polyg
@toc About

    @{b}@{fg highlight}Why is it called Polyglot?@{fg text}@{ub}

    The  main  advantage of Polyglot is its @{b}versatility@{ub}.  Here's the list of
its futures and advantages:

 o  Polyglot  is not a program for learning English or German, it's just for
    learning  @{b}foreign  languages@{ub}.  The only limitation is the possibility of
    displaying  national characters on the screen (no Chinese :^), look also
    at @{" fonts " link FontS}.
 o  You  may  learn  not  only  simple  words  and phrases, but also groups,
    declinations  and practical application in sentences (grammar).  @{b}Form of
    tests@{ub}  is  not  adjusted  to specific applications.  You may choose that
    form,  which  is  best  for  you  and  adjust  it  to  your  needs.  See
    @{" practice " link Pract}.
 o  Data  @{" bases " link Basic}  may  be  divided  into smaller @{" groups " link Basic}, even completely
    different,  which  lets you learn in small steps (and @{" systematically " link Learn}).
 o  This program  is absolutely @{b}system-friendly@{ub}!!!  It's not written in amos
    as many other programs of this kind, but in the great @{" AmigaE " link Copyr}.  It uses
    correctly all system resources (2.0 or higher).
 o  Polyglot  has  a  very  nice  @{" interface " link Inter}, but so simple that it doesn't
    disturb  you  learning (as many pc progs :-).  And it's very @{b}comfortable@{ub}
    (mouse  and  keyboard) - my subjective opinion from a few months of work
    with it.  Gadtools and reqtools used!
 o  It uses its own @{" screen " link PubSc} (also public) with any mode, colour palette and
    font you like (see @{" preferences " link Prefs}).
 o  It  is  @{b}localized@{ub}  since this version!  It's English now (sorry for poor
    translation) and has Polish @{" locales " link Local} too.
 o  Finally - it's @{" shareware " link Share} and you may use it for only 4USD!

@endnode

