@node Autho "About me :-)"
@prev Autho
@toc Endin

    @{b}@{fg highlight}Who is the Author?@{fg text}@{ub}

    My  name  is  @{b}Michal@{ub}  (or Michael if you like) @{b}Mecinski@{ub}, my pseudonym is
@{b}CompLex@{ub}.   I  live  in Poland and I go to the Secondary School (class 2) and
I'm sixteen (yeah, that's correct - April 1998).
    I've had my @{b}Amiga@{ub} for a long time and I started to work in @{b}E@{ub} last year -
here you see the result.  But soon I will have a pc too...  That if @{b}Polyglot@{ub}
will be my last prog depends on you (see @{" Shareware " link Share} again).
    I'm  not  a  member  of  any group (there aren't many good Amigers in my
region).   And  I've been learning the @{b}programming@{ub} myself (there aren't many
books or something :(.

    @{b}@{fg highlight}My Address@{fg text}@{ub}

    Please send all donations (shareware!), propositions, suggestions, asks,
warnings, bug reports etc.  to my snail-mail @{b}address@{ub}:

                      Michal Mecinski
                      Morcinka 22/20
                      43-430 SKOCZOW
                          POLAND

@endnode

@node Copyr "Copyrights"
@toc Endin

    @{b}@{fg highlight}Copyrights@{fg text}@{ub}

    The  Polyglot  is  written  in  the  @{b}AmigaE@{ub}  language V2.1 (© Wouter van
Oortmerssen).
    The  source  code  is  48000 lines and 145000 bytes long, not for public
release.

    The  program  uses  the  @{b}reqtools.library@{ub}  V38 (© Nico François & Magnus
Holmgren).  The V38.1296 is included.

    The  program  uses  the  @{b}locale@{ub}  system  (Polish included).  The catalog
description  and  translation  are  copyright  by  me.   See  the note about
@{" translating " link Local} the program.

    This  documentation  uses  the @{b}AmigaGuide@{ub}®, installation script uses the
@{b}Installer@{ub}® program.  The program uses the @{b}Amiga@{ub}...  ®

    There  is  an  English  version  of  @{b}AFD-Copyright@{ub} (TM) included in this
documentation.

    The icons are done by me, they're modelled on the @{b}MagicWB@{ub} (TM).

    The copyrights for program - see @{" shareware " link Share} and @{" AFD-Copyright " link AfdCo} info.

@endnode

@node Thank "Thanks"
@toc Endin

    @{b}@{fg highlight}Thanks@{fg text}@{ub}

    I  thank  mostly  to  the @{b}BlaBla group@{ub} (greetings, Kysy) for cooperating
with beta-testing and upload the program to Aminet.

    I  thank to the Polish @{b}Amiga Magazine@{ub} editors (mostly to authors of a 'C
for  everyone'  series)  for  being  the  only  source  of information about
@{b}Amiga@{ub}...

    I  thank  to my @{b}close people@{ub} for bearing a half year which I've spent by
the computer :-)

    I  thank  to @{b}everyone@{ub} who likes my program and will @{b}tell@{ub} me (and @{b}support@{ub}
me).

@endnode


@node Local "Polyglot and locale"
@next Local
@toc Endin

    @{b}@{fg highlight}Localization of the program@{fg text}@{ub}

    The   program   has   been  @{b}localized@{ub}  since  1.25  version.  It may use
@{b}@{fg fill}locale.library@{ub}@{fg text}  now.   The  original  built-in  messages are @{b}English@{ub}, in the
@{b}@{fg fill}catalogs@{ub}@{fg text} directory there is a @{b}Polish@{ub} translation.  The documentation is also
translated,  a  new example base is created and the installer script is also
translated.
    If somebody really wants to @{b}translate my program@{ub} to any other languages,
I'm  open  for  propositions.   Well,  but  translating a 110kb doc is not a
pleasure  (not  for  me),  the script and example base should be also done).
The  @{b}catalog  description@{ub}  (and its Polish translation) is available in this
package.   And  maybe  somebody  would  like  to  correct this funny English
translation.  Please contact @{" with me " link Autho}.

@endnode

